com.microfocus.adm.pulse.pluginapi.chain.annotations

Annotation Type PulseChainStepPluginDefinition


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface PulseChainStepPluginDefinition

    Annotation that should be applied to Java implementations of PulseChainStepPlugin to provide default values for groupId, pluginId, version, displayName and description so that the plugin descriptor file, plugin.json, only needs to contain the plugin's className.

    Since:
    19.1.1

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      String groupId
      Plugin's groupId should be modelled on the reversed domain name, like Java package names are.
      String pluginId
      Plugin's pluginId should be a short name that describes what the plugin does and is unique within the groupId.
      String version
      Plugin's version should be an indication of what changes have happened to a particular plugin by giving each release a comparable version.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String category
      An optional readable category for the plugin to present in the UI.
      String description
      An optional readable description of what the plugin does, which may be presented in some parts of the UI.
      String displayName
      An optional readable name for the plugin to present in the UI.

    • Element Detail

      • groupId

        public abstract String groupId

        Plugin's groupId should be modelled on the reversed domain name, like Java package names are. For example, "com.mycompany.pulseplugins". It should contain components that start with a lowercase letter, contain digits or lowercase letters, and are separated by '.'.

        Returns:
        The plugin's group identifier (normally associated with the plugin's author).
        Since:
        19.1.1

      • pluginId

        public abstract String pluginId

        Plugin's pluginId should be a short name that describes what the plugin does and is unique within the groupId. For example, "checklineendings". It should start with a lowercase letter and contain just digits and lowercase letters.

        Returns:
        The plugin's plugin identifier (should uniquely identify this plugin within groupId).
        Since:
        19.1.1

      • version

        public abstract String version

        Plugin's version should be an indication of what changes have happened to a particular plugin by giving each release a comparable version. For example, "1.0.0". It should consist of up to 3 numeric components that are separated by '.'.

        Returns:
        The plugin's version (typically x.y.z, where x, y and z are integers).
        Since:
        19.1.1

      • displayName

        public abstract String displayName

        An optional readable name for the plugin to present in the UI.

        Returns:
        The plugin's presentation name.
        Since:
        19.1.1
        Default:
        ""

      • category

        public abstract String category

        An optional readable category for the plugin to present in the UI.

        Returns:
        The plugin's category name.
        Since:
        19.1.1
        Default:
        "OTHER"

      • description

        public abstract String description

        An optional readable description of what the plugin does, which may be presented in some parts of the UI.

        Returns:
        The plugin's presentation description.
        Since:
        19.1.1
        Default:
        ""
